ctive June 6, 2014; P.A. 14-182 made a technical change in Subdiv. (5)(S), effective June 12, 2014; P.A. 14-212 amended Subdiv. (12) to redefine “quasi-public agency” to include State Education Resource Center, effective June 13, 2014; P.A. 14-217 amended Subdiv. (12) by adding “Connecticut Student Loan Foundation”, deleting “Health Information Technology Exchange of Connecticut” and making technical changes, effective July 1, 2014; P.A. 14-222 amended Subdiv. (12) to redefine “quasi-public agency” to include the Connecticut Port Authority and to make technical changes, effective October 1, 2015; P.A. 15-18 amended Subdiv. (12) to redefine “quasi-public agency” to include the Connecticut Student Loan Foundation and the State Education Resource Center and to delete the Health Information Technology Exchange of Connecticut; June Sp. Sess. P.A. 15-5 amended Subdiv. (12) to redefine “quasi-public agency” to include the Connecticut Port Authority, effective July 1, 2015; P.A. 16-29 amended Subdiv. (12) by adding “the Connecticut Retirement Security Authority” to the definition of “quasi-public agency”, effective July 1, 2016; May Sp. Sess. P.A. 16-3 changed effective date of P.A. 16-29, S. 14, from July 1, 2016, to January 1, 2017, effective June 2, 2016; P.A. 17-237 amended Subdiv. (20) by replacing “technical high school” with “technical education and career school”, effective July 1, 2017; P.A. 19-117 amended Subdiv. (12) by adding “the Connecticut Municipal Redevelopment Authority” to the definition of “quasi-public agency”; P.A. 21-164 amended Subdiv. (12) to redefine “quasi-public agency” to include the Paid Family and Medical Leave Insurance Authority, effective July 1, 2021, amended Subdiv. (5)(D) to make a technical change and add reference to grandparent and added Subdiv. (21) defining “confidential information”, effective October 1, 2021; P.A. 22-118 amended Subdiv. (12) by deleting “the Connecticut Retirement Security Authority,” effective July 1, 2022; P.A. 